cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with the recognition problem of stick graphs, which are intersection graphs of horizontal and vertical line segments. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the complexity of variants of the recognition problem, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper proposes algorithms to solve the recognition problem efficiently, which is related to data structures (cs.DS).
